Redescription of females (n= 10 ). Dorsum : Dorsal shield 580 ( 510–606 ) x 375 ( 320–380 ) (
Fig. 1
). Dorsal shield covers dorsum, bearing 39 pairs setae plus one to two supernumerary Jx setae between J 4 setae. Seta j 1 34 ( 24–38 ). Marginal and anterior podonotal setae moderately long, j 2 45 ( 37–67 ), r 3 63 ( 45–66 ), S 1 62 ( 42–62 ), S 5 50 ( 40–59 ), Z 5 51 ( 39–57 ), J 5 36 ( 28–48 ). Central setae shorter, j 6 45 ( 30–49 ), z 5 42 ( 33–50 ). All setae smooth except Z 5 rarely has a few barbs.

Gnathosoma : Movable
digit 85 ( 62–85 ). Fixed digit with well developed apically divided tip (Gabelzahn) and 3 additional teeth (
Fig. 2
). The two distalmost teeth of the fixed digit are moderately strong and oppose corresponding teeth in the movable digit. The middle tooth is immediately proximal of pilus dentilus. The proximalmost tooth is a much smaller cusp. Internal malae fused medially, fringed, with weak lateral arms that extend to less than half the length of the corniculi. Fimbriae without swollen tips. Corniculi strong, 49 ( 30–49 ) long; h 1 53 ( 38–54 ), h 2 30 ( 16–30 ), h 3 53 ( 40–55 ), capitular setae 39 ( 26–39 ). Deutosternal groove slightly wider anteriorly with 6 (rarely 5 or 7 ) deutosternal rows of ca. 5–8 denticles. Groove flanked by 4 , or rarely 3 , transverse lines. Second cheliceral segment 195 ( 148–202 ), first cheliceral segment 60 ( 48–86 ). Epistome is a simple lobe with a smooth edge (
Fig. 4
)
